him&s;elf in a very muddy &s;oil, behind
three &s;everal fortifications, which do not ex|actly
&s;upport each other. The advocate for
the &s;incerity of Eu&s;ebius maintains: 1&s;t, That
he never made &s;uch a declaration: 2dly, That
he had a right to make it: and, 3dly, That
he did not ob&s;erve it. The&s;e &s;eparate and
