A. D. 302, N^o 11. See likewi&s;e Tille|mont,
Mem. Eccle&s;. tom, v. p. 62. 156;
tom. vii. p. 130.) In a former in&s;tance, Dr.
Chel&s;um appeared to be more credulous than
a Monk: on the pre&s;ent occa&s;ion, he has &s;hewn
